00:16:55,732 --> 00:16:57,699
Over here!

280
00:16:57,734 --> 00:16:58,666
Clement?

281
00:16:58,702 --> 00:17:01,736
Serena, Bonnie,
this is incredible!

282
00:17:01,772 --> 00:17:05,573
This is the Azoth Kingdom!

283
00:17:05,609 --> 00:17:08,543
The Azoth Kingdom?

284
00:17:08,578 --> 00:17:10,578
It's an ultra-mechanized city.

285
00:17:10,614 --> 00:17:12,580
We'll find the great
scientist Nicola

286
00:17:12,616 --> 00:17:14,582
using arcane science and art.

287
00:17:14,618 --> 00:17:15,583
[LAUGHING]

288
00:17:15,619 --> 00:17:18,319
Mechanized?

289
00:17:18,355 --> 00:17:19,621
Nicola was a genius.

290
00:17:19,656 --> 00:17:22,690
He's truly one of
my all-time idols.

291
00:17:22,726 --> 00:17:25,593
He used Pokemon
skills as inspiration

292
00:17:25,629 --> 00:17:27,495
for his many inventions.

293
00:17:27,531 --> 00:17:30,298
Truly a great man.

294
00:17:30,333 --> 00:17:30,765
[INAUDIBLE].

295
00:17:35,772 --> 00:17:38,706
[INAUDIBLE].

296
00:17:38,742 --> 00:17:41,676
[GRUNTING]

297
00:17:41,711 --> 00:17:43,344
[GASPING]

298
00:17:44,381 --> 00:17:46,781
Huh?

299
00:17:46,817 --> 00:17:47,782
[CHUCKLE]

300
00:17:47,818 --> 00:17:49,584
Pikaboo.

301
00:17:49,619 --> 00:17:50,552
[CHUCKLE]

302
00:17:52,789 --> 00:17:54,756
[STOMPING]

303
00:17:54,791 --> 00:17:55,757
[GRUNT]

304
00:17:59,563 --> 00:18:00,695
[ROBOT NOISES]

305
00:18:00,730 --> 00:18:04,599
For you, I would walk
through fire and water.

306
00:18:04,634 --> 00:18:06,301
Pika-pi!

307
00:18:06,336 --> 00:18:07,702
Pikachu!

308
00:18:07,737 --> 00:18:09,604
[ROBOT NOISES]

309
00:18:09,639 --> 00:18:12,307
So they call you
Volcanion, don't they?

310
00:18:12,342 --> 00:18:15,276
Mm, and what do they do?

311
00:18:15,312 --> 00:18:15,743
[ROBOT NOISES]

312
00:18:18,682 --> 00:18:22,717
Magearna, you really are
a one-of-a-kind Pokemon.

313
00:18:22,752 --> 00:18:23,685
Pika.

314
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:25,687
Hahaha.

315
00:18:25,722 --> 00:18:27,355
Magearna, everything OK?

316
00:18:27,390 --> 00:18:28,523
[ROBOT NOISE]

317
00:18:28,558 --> 00:18:31,526
My name's Ash, And
this is my pal Pikachu.

318
00:18:31,561 --> 00:18:32,694
Pika, Pikachu.

319
00:18:32,729 --> 00:18:33,695
[ROBOT NOISE]

320
00:18:33,730 --> 00:18:34,762
[GRUNT]

321
00:18:34,798 --> 00:18:36,598
It's nice to meet you too.

322
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:37,565
[GRUNT]

323
00:18:37,601 --> 00:18:40,368
Don't touch it!

324
00:18:40,403 --> 00:18:41,369
[BELL DINGS]

325
00:18:42,439 --> 00:18:43,371
Pika.

326
00:18:51,681 --> 00:18:53,581
Hey, what are you doing?

327
00:18:53,617 --> 00:18:55,650
I can't blast
anything without water.

328
00:18:55,685 --> 00:18:56,684
You can't?

329
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:57,652
Pika.

330
00:19:00,390 --> 00:19:01,456
Don't worry.

331
00:19:01,491 --> 00:19:04,559
If those guys show up again,
we'll chase them away.

332
00:19:04,594 --> 00:19:07,662
I don't from humans.

333
00:19:07,697 --> 00:19:08,630
Pikachu.

334
00:19:08,665 --> 00:19:10,632
Stay out of this,
electric nuisance.

335
00:19:10,667 --> 00:19:11,699
Pika.

336
00:19:11,735 --> 00:19:12,634
Pika-eh-kachu!

337
00:19:15,572 --> 00:19:16,404
Listen up.

338
00:19:16,439 --> 00:19:18,373
I'll tell you just one.

339
00:19:18,408 --> 00:19:21,643
I will never trust humans.

340
00:19:21,678 --> 00:19:24,546
To Pokemon like you
that cozy up to humans,

341
00:19:24,581 --> 00:19:26,681
I don't trust them either.

342
00:19:26,716 --> 00:19:28,583
Pika, Pika.

343
00:19:28,618 --> 00:19:29,651
What, Pipsqueak?

344
00:19:29,686 --> 00:19:32,654
What to fight?

345
00:19:32,689 --> 00:19:33,621
Come on.

346
00:19:33,657 --> 00:19:35,557
Everybody just calm down now.

347
00:19:35,592 --> 00:19:36,558
[GRUMBLE]

348
00:19:36,593 --> 00:19:37,759
[ROBOT NOISES]

349
00:19:39,596 --> 00:19:40,562
Pik.

350
00:19:40,597 --> 00:19:42,397
Pika.

351
00:19:42,432 --> 00:19:43,698
We found them!

352
00:19:43,733 --> 00:19:46,634
[PANTING] Ash!

353
00:19:46,670 --> 00:19:48,603
everyone!

354
00:19:48,638 --> 00:19:49,604
Huh?

355
00:19:49,639 --> 00:19:52,774
[ROBOT NOISE]

356
00:19:52,809 --> 00:19:54,642
JARVIS: I see.

357
00:19:54,678 --> 00:19:58,313
You say that you know
that young boy trainer.

358
00:19:58,348 --> 00:19:59,714
Boy, do we ever.

359
00:19:59,749 --> 00:20:01,649
Quite-- for a very long time.

360
00:20:01,685 --> 00:20:02,617
Too long.

361
00:20:02,652 --> 00:20:03,685
You have no idea.

362
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,720
And you call
yourselves Team Rocket.

363
00:20:05,755 --> 00:20:06,788
I'll need more information.

364
00:20:06,823 --> 00:20:08,423
TOGETHER: More?

365
00:20:08,458 --> 00:20:09,390
Sure!

366
00:20:12,762 --> 00:20:15,396
Just meeting the
mythical Pokemon Volcanion

367
00:20:15,432 --> 00:20:16,631
would've been amazing.

368
00:20:16,666 --> 00:20:20,401
But to actually meet Nicola's
greatest creation of all time?

369
00:20:20,437 --> 00:20:21,703
I'm honored!

370
00:20:21,738 --> 00:20:22,704
[ROBOT NOISE]

371
00:20:22,739 --> 00:20:23,671
Mm.

372
00:20:23,707 --> 00:20:24,672
[CRACKLE]

373
00:20:24,708 --> 00:20:27,375
Huh?

374
00:20:27,410 --> 00:20:28,409
It's never coming off.

375
00:20:28,445 --> 00:20:29,377
Pika.

376
00:20:29,412 --> 00:20:31,746
You humans are useless.

377
00:20:31,781 --> 00:20:32,747
That's not nice.

378
00:20:32,782 --> 00:20:34,582
[INAUDIBLE].

379
00:20:34,618 --> 00:20:35,416
I'm sorry.

380
00:20:35,452 --> 00:20:36,618
Please forgive me.

381
00:20:36,653 --> 00:20:37,652
Huh?

382
00:20:37,687 --> 00:20:38,620
[GASP]

383
00:20:38,655 --> 00:20:41,589
[ROBOT NOISES]

384
00:20:41,625 --> 00:20:44,392
[DELIGHTED GASP]

385
00:20:44,427 --> 00:20:45,760
Thank you, Magearna.

386
00:20:45,795 --> 00:20:47,629
You're a Pokemon treasure.

387
00:20:47,664 --> 00:20:48,830
Don't touch it!

388
00:20:48,865 --> 00:20:49,831
Huh?

389
00:20:49,866 --> 00:20:51,366
Look out!

390
00:20:51,401 --> 00:20:51,799
Wah!

391
00:20:51,835 --> 00:20:53,768
Pika!

392
00:20:53,803 --> 00:20:55,737
[GROANING]

393
00:20:57,874 --> 00:20:59,474
Why me?

394
00:20:59,509 --> 00:21:00,441
Ugh.

395
00:21:00,477 --> 00:21:01,442
(SADLY) Pika.

396
00:21:01,478 --> 00:21:02,410
Hi, there!

397
00:21:02,445 --> 00:21:03,444
We're back!

398
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:04,579
Huh?

399
00:21:04,614 --> 00:21:05,446
Magearna?

400
00:21:09,386 --> 00:21:10,618
[ROBOT NOISE]

401
00:21:10,654 --> 00:21:11,619
[AMAZED GASPS]

402
00:21:11,688 --> 00:21:12,620
Amazing!

403
00:21:12,656 --> 00:21:13,788
Incredible!

404
00:21:13,823 --> 00:21:14,789
[LAUGHING]

405
00:21:14,824 --> 00:21:16,457
Kind of like a Poke Ball.

406
00:21:16,493 --> 00:21:17,759
- Pikachu.
- Ash?

407
00:21:17,794 --> 00:21:18,760
Huh?

408
00:21:18,795 --> 00:21:19,894
Tada!

409
00:21:19,929 --> 00:21:23,698
Since your clothes are a
mess, how about you try these?

410
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:26,334
Hmm.

411
00:21:26,369 --> 00:21:28,770
Uh-- hmm.

412
00:21:28,805 --> 00:21:30,705
Wow, you look great.

413
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:31,639
Really?

414
00:21:31,675 --> 00:21:33,675
Pikachu, Magearna, do I?

415
00:21:33,710 --> 00:21:35,343
Pika-Pika!

416
00:21:35,378 --> 00:21:37,345
[EXCITED ROBOT NOISE]

417
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:39,614
Stop it, Magearna.

418
00:21:39,649 --> 00:21:41,482
Don't get involved
with these humans.

419
00:21:41,518 --> 00:21:44,752
[ROBOT NOISES]

420
00:21:44,788 --> 00:21:46,421
I refuse.

421
00:21:46,456 --> 00:21:47,488
[ROBOT NOISES]

422
00:21:47,524 --> 00:21:48,456
Leave me alone!

423
00:21:48,491 --> 00:21:50,358
[ROBOT NOISES]

424
00:21:52,395 --> 00:21:53,361
[POOF]

425
00:21:53,396 --> 00:21:54,629
[GASP]

426
00:21:58,668 --> 00:22:01,469
[GEARING UP TO SNEEZE]

427
00:22:02,472 --> 00:22:03,771
[ROARING]

428
00:22:03,807 --> 00:22:04,739
Choo!

429
00:22:09,446 --> 00:22:10,545
[GRUMBLE]

430
00:22:10,580 --> 00:22:13,381
Hey, I told you to
quit it, didn't I?

431
00:22:16,119 --> 00:22:16,617
OK, fine.

432
00:22:16,653 --> 00:22:18,419
I'll doing my best.

433
00:22:18,488 --> 00:22:21,122
[ROBOT NOISES]

434
00:22:22,459 --> 00:22:23,424
[SPLASH]

435
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:24,292
Aah!

436
00:22:24,327 --> 00:22:25,226
Magearna!

437
00:22:28,231 --> 00:22:30,164
[ALL GRUNTING]

438
00:22:34,237 --> 00:22:35,503
Are you all right?

439
00:22:35,538 --> 00:22:38,206
[ROBOT NOISES]

440
00:22:41,177 --> 00:22:42,410
Magearna, you're soaking wet.

441
00:22:42,445 --> 00:22:45,179
We'll get you all dried up.

442
00:22:45,215 --> 00:22:46,414
[ROBOT NOISES]

443
00:22:46,483 --> 00:22:48,216
Well, that's a relief.

444
00:22:48,251 --> 00:22:50,485
Though you've got to
admit, Magearna's heavy.

445
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:52,220
[ROBOT NOISES]

446
00:22:53,189 --> 00:22:54,155
Gearna?

447
00:22:54,190 --> 00:22:55,156
Pika?

448
00:22:55,191 --> 00:22:58,426
It looks embarrassed.

449
00:22:58,461 --> 00:22:59,560
Because it fell?

450
00:22:59,596 --> 00:23:03,131
I don't like Magearna
likes being called heavy.

451
00:23:03,166 --> 00:23:04,465
You're kidding.

452
00:23:04,501 --> 00:23:07,135
Of course it
doesn't like that.

453
00:23:07,170 --> 00:23:08,469
[GASP]

454
00:23:08,505 --> 00:23:10,204
I'm so very sorry.

455
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:11,205
Please forgive me.

456
00:23:11,241 --> 00:23:13,407
Clemont means
well, but he just

457
00:23:13,443 --> 00:23:15,209
doesn't understand some things.

458
00:23:15,245 --> 00:23:16,244
[GIGGLE]

459
00:23:16,279 --> 00:23:17,178
We should go.

460
00:23:17,213 --> 00:23:18,279
The sun is setting.

461
00:23:18,314 --> 00:23:20,481
[ROBOT NOISES]

462
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:26,254
No.

463
00:23:26,289 --> 00:23:29,524
I said, no!

464
00:23:29,559 --> 00:23:33,427
I won't bring humans along.

465
00:23:33,463 --> 00:23:35,396
Hey, where you going?

466
00:23:35,431 --> 00:23:38,399
Come back!

467
00:23:38,434 --> 00:23:39,400
Huh?

468
00:23:39,435 --> 00:23:42,103
Not again.

469
00:23:42,138 --> 00:23:43,571
[YELLING]

470
00:23:45,341 --> 00:23:46,274
Pika-pi!

471
00:23:48,611 --> 00:23:49,544
Huh?

472
00:23:49,579 --> 00:23:52,146
[MURMURING]

473
00:23:54,217 --> 00:23:57,585
We need to get away right now.

474
00:23:57,620 --> 00:24:00,121
[ROBOT NOISES]

475
00:24:00,156 --> 00:24:01,455
Get moving, or I'll
leave you behind.

476
00:24:12,335 --> 00:24:14,168
Raleigh, wait.

477
00:24:14,204 --> 00:24:15,136
Chymia!

478
00:24:15,171 --> 00:24:16,170
What is it?

479
00:24:16,206 --> 00:24:18,539
I saw you standing up
on the tower wall before.

480
00:24:18,575 --> 00:24:21,175
And you were with Alva, as well.

481
00:24:21,211 --> 00:24:22,176
What were you up to?

482
00:24:22,212 --> 00:24:24,312
A scientific investigation.

483
00:24:24,347 --> 00:24:26,314
Many of the amazing
machines built by Nicola

484
00:24:26,349 --> 00:24:28,282
are operating even now.

485
00:24:28,318 --> 00:24:29,517
Oh, is that all?

486
00:24:29,552 --> 00:24:31,085
Listen to me.

487
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:33,287
If you really want to
learn, look to the future,

488
00:24:33,323 --> 00:24:34,522
not just to the past.

489
00:24:34,557 --> 00:24:35,623
The future?

490
00:24:35,658 --> 00:24:38,125
To do that, you need to
learn about the past, see?

491
00:24:42,131 --> 00:24:44,332
Father is worried
about you, as well.

492
00:24:44,367 --> 00:24:47,235
Alva was with me, so
there was no need to worry.

493
00:24:47,270 --> 00:24:49,570
But that's why he's worried.

494
00:24:49,606 --> 00:24:51,339
Now, you know that
father trusts Alva

495
00:24:51,374 --> 00:24:53,474
completely, just like I do.

496
00:24:53,509 --> 00:24:59,146
He thinks a lot more about our
kingdom's future than you do.

497
00:24:59,182 --> 00:25:02,316
So if you'll please
excuse me, I have to go.

498
00:25:13,296 --> 00:25:15,062
1, 2--

499
00:25:15,098 --> 00:25:16,264
BOTH: Ta-da!

500
00:25:16,299 --> 00:25:17,231
Whoa!

501
00:25:17,267 --> 00:25:20,268
Isn't it cute, Volcanion?

502
00:25:20,303 --> 00:25:22,503
[BLOOPING]

503
00:25:25,508 --> 00:25:27,108
[SIGH]

504
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:32,513
Huh?

505
00:25:32,548 --> 00:25:34,482
Well, that went over well.

506
00:25:34,517 --> 00:25:36,117
Maybe it's shy.

507
00:25:36,152 --> 00:25:37,084
Could be.

508
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:38,152
Right, Magearna?

509
00:25:38,187 --> 00:25:40,221
[BEEPING]

510
00:25:40,256 --> 00:25:41,555
Getting friendly, aren't they?

511
00:25:41,591 --> 00:25:43,324
Sure are.

512
00:25:43,359 --> 00:25:46,494
Since we're stuck together
now, might as well have fun.

513
00:25:46,529 --> 00:25:48,296
- I agree.
- Nonsense.

514
00:25:48,331 --> 00:25:50,097
I just want to
get away from you.

515
00:25:50,133 --> 00:25:52,199
Nothing good comes from
interacting with humans.

516
00:25:52,235 --> 00:25:53,134
Huh?

517
00:25:53,169 --> 00:25:54,502
You fell out of the
sky with these bands.

518
00:25:54,537 --> 00:25:55,369
Remember?

519
00:25:55,405 --> 00:25:57,571
Look, humans
made these things.

520
00:25:57,607 --> 00:25:59,340
Well, it sure wasn't us.

521
00:25:59,375 --> 00:26:01,208
All humans are the same.

522
00:26:01,244 --> 00:26:02,176
Pika!

523
00:26:06,282 --> 00:26:07,315
Hey, you.

524
00:26:07,350 --> 00:26:10,184
What are you doing
hanging around like that?

525
00:26:10,219 --> 00:26:13,187
Get your filthy
human hands off me.

526
00:26:13,222 --> 00:26:14,188
No, I won't!

527
00:26:14,223 --> 00:26:15,189
Cut it out, I said.

528
00:26:15,224 --> 00:26:16,490
No, you first!

529
00:26:16,526 --> 00:26:18,492
I'll blast you off.

530
00:26:27,570 --> 00:26:28,502
Agh.

531
00:26:32,342 --> 00:26:34,108
JARVIS: If they're
headed somewhere,

532
00:26:34,143 --> 00:26:36,510
it's probably Nebel Plateau.

533
00:26:36,546 --> 00:26:39,246
Oh, the place with the field
of flowers where Magearna was

534
00:26:39,282 --> 00:26:40,214
found.

535
00:26:40,249 --> 00:26:42,216
Yes.

536
00:26:42,251 --> 00:26:45,486
Members of Team Rocket,
please go investigate.

537
00:26:45,521 --> 00:26:47,288
Count on us, sir!

538
00:26:47,323 --> 00:26:49,290
[GIGGLING]

539
00:26:49,325 --> 00:26:51,158
It's all finished!

540
00:26:51,194 --> 00:26:52,093
What is?

541
00:26:52,128 --> 00:26:53,527
Have a look for yourselves.

542
00:26:53,563 --> 00:26:56,230
The future is now,
thanks to science.

543
00:27:01,170 --> 00:27:04,071
I made this protective
suits inspired by moves

544
00:27:04,107 --> 00:27:06,107
like iron defense and protect.

545
00:27:06,142 --> 00:27:07,341
It's called Mr. Iron Defense.

546
00:27:07,377 --> 00:27:08,309
Whoa-ho!

547
00:27:11,147 --> 00:27:13,247
You're protected from
any kind of attack.

548
00:27:15,385 --> 00:27:16,317
Huh?

549
00:27:16,352 --> 00:27:18,152
What do I see?

550
00:27:18,187 --> 00:27:20,054
It looks like a camp fire.

551
00:27:20,089 --> 00:27:22,223
Maybe they're setting
up camp here tonight.

552
00:27:22,258 --> 00:27:24,125
We have to tell Alva.

553
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:25,092
Wait.

554
00:27:25,128 --> 00:27:27,261
Our real boss is the prince.

555
00:27:27,296 --> 00:27:30,264
Once we can get our hands on
what he wants, we'll be rich.

556
00:27:30,299 --> 00:27:31,332
Brilliant!

557
00:27:31,367 --> 00:27:33,067
And that's rich.

558
00:27:33,102 --> 00:27:34,368
Let's make some dough.

559
00:27:34,404 --> 00:27:37,371
[SNORING]

560
00:27:41,577 --> 00:27:42,410
Huh?

561
00:27:42,445 --> 00:27:44,111
You sensed it, too?

562
00:27:52,388 --> 00:27:53,354
Pika.

563
00:27:53,389 --> 00:27:54,321
Pikachu!

564
00:27:57,193 --> 00:27:58,125
Ah!

565
00:27:58,161 --> 00:28:00,061
Huh?

566
00:28:00,096 --> 00:28:02,229
Uh, Magearna!

567
00:28:02,265 --> 00:28:04,231
[BEEPING]

568
00:28:04,267 --> 00:28:05,332
JAMES: Yoo-hoo!

569
00:28:05,368 --> 00:28:07,301
ALL: Huh?

570
00:28:07,336 --> 00:28:09,270
From now on,
Magearna's our guest.

571
00:28:09,305 --> 00:28:10,271
Team Rocket?

572
00:28:10,306 --> 00:28:12,073
What are you guys doing here?

573
00:28:12,108 --> 00:28:12,640
Huh?

574
00:28:12,675 --> 00:28:14,208
Heracross and Pinsir?

575
00:28:14,243 --> 00:28:16,310
Hey, where are
your normal Pokemon?

576
00:28:16,345 --> 00:28:19,046
We're not your
normal Team Rocket.

577
00:28:19,082 --> 00:28:19,947
Check this out.

578
00:28:19,982 --> 00:28:22,383
TEAM ROCKET: Mega
Wave Team Rocket!

579
00:28:22,418 --> 00:28:23,350
What?

580
00:28:23,419 --> 00:28:25,219
Key Stones!

581
00:28:25,254 --> 00:28:28,222
We joined forces with
the good Prince Raleigh.

582
00:28:28,257 --> 00:28:29,156
No way!

583
00:28:29,192 --> 00:28:30,124
See?

584
00:28:30,159 --> 00:28:31,358
We're Mega Wave Team Rocket!

585
00:28:34,363 --> 00:28:35,262
[GASP]

586
00:28:35,298 --> 00:28:36,263
Pika.

587
00:28:36,299 --> 00:28:37,231
Mega Wave!

588
00:28:47,176 --> 00:28:48,109
[SNARLING]

589
00:28:48,144 --> 00:28:49,276
Mega Evolve?

590
00:28:49,312 --> 00:28:50,244
But how?

591
00:28:50,279 --> 00:28:52,213
To Mega Evolve, there
must be a close bond

592
00:28:52,248 --> 00:28:54,181
between trainer and Pokemon.

593
00:28:54,217 --> 00:28:58,252
It's thanks to what Alva
calls-- er, what was it?

594
00:28:58,287 --> 00:28:59,220
Mm.

595
00:28:59,255 --> 00:29:01,355
Neo arcane science.

596
00:29:01,390 --> 00:29:04,091
With this technology, we
can use Mega Evolution

597
00:29:04,127 --> 00:29:06,093
and we don't need
any stinking bond!

598
00:29:06,129 --> 00:29:07,128
I see.

599
00:29:07,163 --> 00:29:08,395
So Gengar and the others--

600
00:29:08,431 --> 00:29:10,397
[SNARLING]

601
00:29:10,433 --> 00:29:12,166
Gengar!

602
00:29:12,201 --> 00:29:14,101
What about how
the Pokemon feel?

603
00:29:14,137 --> 00:29:16,070
That's not Mega Evolution!

604
00:29:16,105 --> 00:29:18,105
Arcane science was
developed to make

605
00:29:18,141 --> 00:29:19,306
people and Pokemon happy!

606
00:29:19,342 --> 00:29:22,243
You're defaming the
memory of Nicola!

607
00:29:22,278 --> 00:29:23,210
Hey!

608
00:29:23,246 --> 00:29:26,080
We call it neo because
technology passed

609
00:29:26,115 --> 00:29:27,348
through by science, guys.

610
00:29:27,383 --> 00:29:28,282
Now, Heracross!

611
00:29:28,317 --> 00:29:29,250
Pinsir, too!

612
00:29:29,285 --> 00:29:33,053
Turn them into goo!

613
00:29:33,089 --> 00:29:34,155
[SCREAMING]

614
00:29:34,190 --> 00:29:36,357
You, take Magearna
away from here.

615
00:29:36,392 --> 00:29:39,293
I hate relying on humans,
but I have no choice.

616
00:29:39,328 --> 00:29:41,061
Go!

617
00:29:41,097 --> 00:29:42,062
Everyone, do it.

618
00:29:42,098 --> 00:29:43,063
All right.

619
00:29:43,099 --> 00:29:43,497
Let's go, Magearna.

620
00:29:43,533 --> 00:29:46,267
Leave it to us.

621
00:29:46,302 --> 00:29:49,170
Let 'er rip.

622
00:29:49,205 --> 00:29:50,304
Pikachu, use Thunderbolt!

623
00:29:50,339 --> 00:29:51,272
Pikachu!

624
00:30:04,453 --> 00:30:05,386
Get him, Volcanion!

625
00:30:05,421 --> 00:30:07,288
I don't need a cheerleader.

626
00:30:18,534 --> 00:30:19,500
Yes!

627
00:30:19,535 --> 00:30:20,467
Pika.

628
00:30:29,378 --> 00:30:31,145
[SCREAMING]

629
00:30:32,515 --> 00:30:33,480
Success!

630
00:30:33,516 --> 00:30:36,183
It worked like a charm.

631
00:30:36,219 --> 00:30:39,186
Mega Evolution
drew Volcanion away.

632
00:30:39,222 --> 00:30:41,188
[SCREAMING]

633
00:30:41,457 --> 00:30:42,389
Gardevoir.

634
00:30:46,195 --> 00:30:47,161
The nerve!

635
00:30:58,341 --> 00:31:01,308
Gardevoir, Mega Evolve!

636
00:31:01,344 --> 00:31:02,276
Gard!

637
00:31:11,254 --> 00:31:12,286
Gardevoir.

638
00:31:12,321 --> 00:31:14,388
MEOWTH: Now there's a
Mega Gardevoir in my face.

639
00:31:14,423 --> 00:31:16,223
Use Dazzling Gleam!

640
00:31:16,259 --> 00:31:17,191
Gardevoir!

641
00:31:24,433 --> 00:31:27,201
TEAM ROCKET: We're
blasting off again!

642
00:31:27,236 --> 00:31:29,169
[SCREAMING]

643
00:31:36,412 --> 00:31:37,311
Wow!

644
00:31:37,346 --> 00:31:38,279
Nothing.

645
00:31:43,519 --> 00:31:44,485
Pikachu!

646
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:45,486
PIKACHU: Pika.

647
00:31:45,521 --> 00:31:47,488
Let 'em have it, Volcanion.

648
00:31:47,523 --> 00:31:49,256
Don't blame me
for the results.

649
00:31:49,292 --> 00:31:50,257
Don't worry.

650
00:32:06,409 --> 00:32:07,441
Pika Pika!

651
00:32:07,476 --> 00:32:09,476
Science is so amazing.

652
00:32:09,512 --> 00:32:10,477
Pika?

653
00:32:10,513 --> 00:32:11,445
Huh?

654
00:32:21,257 --> 00:32:23,157
So this is your real power.

655
00:32:23,192 --> 00:32:24,391
Ha.

656
00:32:24,427 --> 00:32:27,194
If I showed you my real power,
it wouldn't be just this.

657
00:32:27,229 --> 00:32:28,529
I've leveled a whole mountain.

658
00:32:28,564 --> 00:32:30,331
Awesome.

659
00:32:30,366 --> 00:32:31,298
Pika?

660
00:32:35,304 --> 00:32:36,470
Hey, Ash!

661
00:32:36,505 --> 00:32:38,505
What exploded?

662
00:32:38,541 --> 00:32:40,474
Hey, guys.

663
00:32:40,509 --> 00:32:41,442
Pika!

664
00:32:41,477 --> 00:32:43,344
Now I've got even more humans.

665
00:32:49,218 --> 00:32:52,519
Magearna, I'm Chymia,
princess of Azoth.

666
00:32:52,555 --> 00:32:55,255
Pleased to meet you.

667
00:32:55,291 --> 00:32:57,491
I'm a descendant of
the Azoth royal family.

668
00:32:57,526 --> 00:32:58,459
Princess?

669
00:32:58,494 --> 00:32:59,393
Whoa.

670
00:32:59,428 --> 00:33:00,427
[BEEPING]

671
00:33:19,281 --> 00:33:21,315
[BEEPING]

672
00:33:21,350 --> 00:33:22,316
[GASP]

673
00:33:22,351 --> 00:33:23,250
Oh, my.

674
00:33:23,285 --> 00:33:24,385
They're beautiful.

675
00:33:24,420 --> 00:33:25,519
Thank you.

676
00:33:25,554 --> 00:33:29,456
Volcanion, you were
protecting Magearna, right?

677
00:33:32,261 --> 00:33:33,193
Hm.

678
00:33:36,949 --> 00:33:38,215
CHYMIA: For the kingdom?

679
00:33:38,250 --> 00:33:40,117
That's what Raleigh said, huh?

680
00:33:40,152 --> 00:33:41,118
SERENA: Right.

681
00:33:41,153 --> 00:33:42,386
One thing's for sure.

682
00:33:42,421 --> 00:33:46,223
Raleigh believes everything that
Alva tells him-- that it's all

683
00:33:46,258 --> 00:33:48,092
for the good of the kingdom.

684
00:33:48,127 --> 00:33:51,128
Does Raleigh really trust
this Alva person that much?

685
00:33:51,163 --> 00:33:52,096
Yes.

686
00:33:55,201 --> 00:33:59,103
Ever since Raleigh was a
boy, he always adored Nicola.

687
00:33:59,138 --> 00:34:02,039
Many times, he would spend
the entire day in his room,

688
00:34:02,074 --> 00:34:06,810
reading old texts and
performing experiments.

689
00:34:06,846 --> 00:34:09,279
And because of that, when he
found out that Councilor Alva

690
00:34:09,315 --> 00:34:12,082
was an arcane
science researcher,

691
00:34:12,118 --> 00:34:15,018
he started to spend more
and more time with him.

692
00:34:19,291 --> 00:34:22,826
So now, since my brother
is involved in this,

693
00:34:22,862 --> 00:34:24,161
that means that I am, too.

694
00:34:27,066 --> 00:34:28,198
[YELLING]

695
00:34:31,003 --> 00:34:32,236
Hey, why don't we
just get on board

696
00:34:32,271 --> 00:34:34,037
the thing they're riding on?

697
00:34:34,073 --> 00:34:36,173
Why would I board
something humans built?

698
00:34:36,208 --> 00:34:39,309
Oh, come on.

699
00:34:39,345 --> 00:34:40,277
Ah!

700
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:49,253
[GASP]

701
00:34:49,288 --> 00:34:51,188
The princess.

702
00:34:51,223 --> 00:34:53,323
I know.

703
00:34:53,359 --> 00:34:54,324
Dedenne.

704
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:55,292
Wow!

705
00:34:55,327 --> 00:34:56,260
A field of flowers!

706
00:35:01,267 --> 00:35:04,001
Come to greet us, huh?

707
00:35:04,036 --> 00:35:06,003
[FRANTIC CHIRPING]

708
00:35:06,038 --> 00:35:07,004
What?

709
00:35:07,039 --> 00:35:08,972
[CHIRP]

710
00:35:09,008 --> 00:35:10,174
Ah?

711
00:35:10,209 --> 00:35:11,175
Ah!

712
00:35:11,210 --> 00:35:12,976
Huh?

713
00:35:13,012 --> 00:35:15,846
[CHIRPING]

714
00:35:15,881 --> 00:35:16,847
Up ahead.

715
00:35:16,882 --> 00:35:18,081
Is that Amaura?

716
00:35:23,289 --> 00:35:26,089
Amaura's badly injured.

717
00:35:26,125 --> 00:35:28,225
Hold on.

718
00:35:28,260 --> 00:35:29,226
[WHIMPERING]

719
00:35:31,263 --> 00:35:32,196
Hang in there.

720
00:35:36,135 --> 00:35:37,301
We'll take care of it.

721
00:35:37,336 --> 00:35:39,002
I don't need your help.

722
00:35:39,038 --> 00:35:40,103
I'll carry Amaura myself.

723
00:35:46,011 --> 00:35:47,144
[GROANING]

724
00:35:48,180 --> 00:35:49,112
[GRUNTING]

725
00:35:53,085 --> 00:35:55,319
Now this big one
will fetch me an even

726
00:35:55,354 --> 00:35:57,221
better price than that Amaura.

727
00:35:57,256 --> 00:36:00,991
A Pokemon hunter.

728
00:36:01,026 --> 00:36:03,160
[POWERING DOWN]

729
00:36:03,195 --> 00:36:04,161
[GASP]

730
00:36:04,196 --> 00:36:06,196
All right,
Pikachu, Thunderbolt!

731
00:36:06,232 --> 00:36:07,130
Pikachu!

732
00:36:10,870 --> 00:36:13,837
I'll fix all of you.

733
00:36:13,873 --> 00:36:15,138
[GROWLING]

734
00:36:37,997 --> 00:36:40,197
[CHIRPING]

735
00:36:40,232 --> 00:36:41,999
What a bad man.

736
00:36:42,034 --> 00:36:44,301
Pokemon hunters
only want one thing--

737
00:36:44,370 --> 00:36:47,037
to make money stealing Pokemon.

738
00:36:47,072 --> 00:36:50,007
So bad things like this--
do they happen a lot?

739
00:36:50,042 --> 00:36:51,108
Yes.

740
00:36:51,143 --> 00:36:54,011
But I can usually drive
them off by creating mist

741
00:36:54,046 --> 00:36:55,846
long before they get this far.

742
00:37:06,292 --> 00:37:07,257
[GASP]

743
00:37:07,293 --> 00:37:08,225
Pika.

744
00:37:13,065 --> 00:37:16,033
VOLCANION: This is
Nebel Plateau, our home.

745
00:37:23,108 --> 00:37:24,274
So many Pokemon!

746
00:37:24,310 --> 00:37:26,209
And they're totally cute!

747
00:37:36,889 --> 00:37:38,155
[BEEPING]

748
00:37:38,891 --> 00:37:40,123
- Drill.
- Pika, pika.

749
00:37:40,159 --> 00:37:41,091
Pika!

750
00:37:41,126 --> 00:37:43,093
Dedenne.

751
00:37:43,128 --> 00:37:44,061
Pika?

752
00:37:44,096 --> 00:37:45,262
Dedenne.

753
00:37:45,297 --> 00:37:47,898
Everybody seems
pretty afraid of us.

754
00:37:47,933 --> 00:37:49,132
You know why.

755
00:37:49,168 --> 00:37:50,934
You're humans, right?

756
00:37:50,970 --> 00:37:53,837
It does look like they
don't trust us at all.

757
00:37:53,872 --> 00:37:55,038
I wonder why that is.

758
00:38:00,212 --> 00:38:01,144
All right.

759
00:38:01,180 --> 00:38:02,879
I'll treat Amaura.
Don't worry.

760
00:38:02,915 --> 00:38:03,847
Treat.

761
00:38:03,882 --> 00:38:06,216
Don't just do whatever you want.

762
00:38:06,251 --> 00:38:07,184
Don't be so angry.

763
00:38:07,219 --> 00:38:10,120
You've got to trust
us a little bit.

764
00:38:10,155 --> 00:38:11,088
[BEEPING]

765
00:38:11,123 --> 00:38:12,856
You help, too, Bonnie.
BONNIE: Sure!

766
00:38:12,891 --> 00:38:13,890
CHYMIA: Let me help, too.

767
00:38:13,926 --> 00:38:14,925
I could help, too.

768
00:38:20,265 --> 00:38:21,832
Does it sting?

769
00:38:21,867 --> 00:38:22,899
It'll all be over soon.

770
00:38:22,935 --> 00:38:24,801
You've just got to be strong.

771
00:38:24,837 --> 00:38:25,268
Pika.

772
00:38:30,976 --> 00:38:33,076
CHYMIA: The bandage is freezing.

773
00:38:33,112 --> 00:38:36,046
This sort of thing happens
with ice type Pokemon.

774
00:38:36,081 --> 00:38:37,848
It's proof of the healing.

775
00:38:37,883 --> 00:38:39,182
That means the
medicine's working.

776
00:38:39,218 --> 00:38:41,284
Amaura, that's so great.

777
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:42,285
Dedenne-ne.

778
00:38:42,321 --> 00:38:44,187
Amaura.

779
00:38:44,223 --> 00:38:46,256
Forget all the bad times.

780
00:38:46,291 --> 00:38:48,291
You're in a safe place now.

781
00:38:48,327 --> 00:38:49,860
You have food here.

782
00:38:49,895 --> 00:38:51,294
You have friends, too.

783
00:38:51,330 --> 00:38:53,230
'Maura.

784
00:38:53,265 --> 00:38:54,831
Sleep now, Amaura.

785
00:38:58,871 --> 00:39:00,070
[BEEPING]

786
00:39:03,208 --> 00:39:06,843
[LULLABY MUSIC PLAYING]

787
00:39:15,220 --> 00:39:16,153
Pika!

788
00:39:48,220 --> 00:39:49,186
Pi?

789
00:39:49,221 --> 00:39:50,153
Huh?

790
00:39:53,192 --> 00:39:56,126
Pika?

791
00:39:56,161 --> 00:39:57,828
Pika.

792
00:39:57,863 --> 00:40:00,263
It must be that they're
scared because we're here.

793
00:40:00,299 --> 00:40:04,234
Well, we may be humans, but
Pokemon are still Pokemon.

794
00:40:04,269 --> 00:40:05,235
All right.

795
00:40:05,270 --> 00:40:07,237
Now, everybody out!

796
00:40:11,944 --> 00:40:13,977
Pancha-cha.

797
00:40:14,012 --> 00:40:15,245
Yeah!
Great idea.

798
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:16,213
I'm in.

799
00:40:19,184 --> 00:40:20,016
Hawlucha.

800
00:40:20,052 --> 00:40:21,251
Talonflame.

801
00:40:21,286 --> 00:40:23,854
Bla, bluh.

802
00:40:23,889 --> 00:40:24,855
Bun!
Bunnelby!

803
00:40:24,890 --> 00:40:25,322
Luxray.

804
00:40:25,357 --> 00:40:26,289
You see?

805
00:40:26,325 --> 00:40:28,859
You don't need to
be afraid of us.

806
00:40:28,894 --> 00:40:32,262
Help us show them
we're friendly.

807
00:40:32,297 --> 00:40:33,230
Pikachu!

808
00:40:39,271 --> 00:40:41,204
Ch-ch-ch cha-cha-chu.

809
00:40:41,240 --> 00:40:42,239
Che.

810
00:40:42,274 --> 00:40:43,173
Eee!

811
00:40:46,278 --> 00:40:47,177
Chu!

812
00:40:53,318 --> 00:40:54,985
Hawlucha.

813
00:40:55,020 --> 00:40:56,920
Cha-cha.

814
00:40:56,955 --> 00:40:57,921
Lucha.

815
00:40:57,956 --> 00:40:58,889
Lucha!

816
00:40:58,924 --> 00:40:59,356
Pikachu.

817
00:41:23,348 --> 00:41:25,015
[BEEPING]

818
00:41:25,050 --> 00:41:26,016
Wow, this is great!

819
00:41:26,051 --> 00:41:26,983
Yeah!

820
00:41:29,354 --> 00:41:30,287
Argh.

821
00:41:30,322 --> 00:41:32,222
Huh?

822
00:41:32,257 --> 00:41:33,924
Volcanion, are you OK?

823
00:41:33,959 --> 00:41:37,027
Hey, wait a minute--
the Pokemon hunter.

824
00:41:37,062 --> 00:41:38,295
You need help, too.

825
00:41:38,330 --> 00:41:39,930
I need nothing.

826
00:41:39,965 --> 00:41:43,166
Magearna, stay out of the
flower field for a while, OK?

827
00:41:45,971 --> 00:41:47,170
But what about you?

828
00:41:50,209 --> 00:41:51,041
Hey!

829
00:41:51,076 --> 00:41:52,008
Wait for me!

830
00:41:52,044 --> 00:41:52,976
Bonnie.

831
00:42:05,023 --> 00:42:07,224
ASH: It's a hot spring.

832
00:42:07,259 --> 00:42:08,992
BONNIE: Like a giant bath.

833
00:42:09,027 --> 00:42:11,995
A bath will fix me right up.

834
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:12,963
Wow.

835
00:42:22,241 --> 00:42:26,009
Quick, Ash, you've got to
get out of there right away.

836
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:27,877
Wha?

837
00:42:27,913 --> 00:42:28,878
Whoa!

838
00:42:28,914 --> 00:42:32,182
Your suit's
absorbing the water.

839
00:42:32,217 --> 00:42:33,883
[YELLING]

840
00:42:40,926 --> 00:42:42,192
Eugh, and then some.

841
00:42:46,231 --> 00:42:47,163
Hm.

842
00:42:47,199 --> 00:42:49,299
You humans are an
annoying bunch.

843
00:42:58,977 --> 00:42:59,876
Wrench, please.

844
00:42:59,911 --> 00:43:01,278
Bunnelby.

845
00:43:01,313 --> 00:43:03,013
Che.

846
00:43:03,048 --> 00:43:03,980
Thanks a lot.

847
00:43:09,221 --> 00:43:11,921
Working on gadgets
along with Pokemon.

848
00:43:11,957 --> 00:43:15,258
I'm sure it must have been
like this for Nicola, too.

849
00:43:15,294 --> 00:43:18,228
Nicola thought the world
needed both humans and Pokemon

850
00:43:18,263 --> 00:43:21,298
to be in harmony, which I
believe is what inspired

851
00:43:21,333 --> 00:43:23,833
him to create Magearna.

852
00:43:23,869 --> 00:43:26,236
Magearna's the living
embodiment of the philosophy

853
00:43:26,271 --> 00:43:28,972
of arcane science.

854
00:43:29,007 --> 00:43:32,242
At least, that's the way I
prefer to interpret that.

855
00:43:32,277 --> 00:43:34,010
It's such a beautiful idea.

856
00:43:38,250 --> 00:43:41,084
ASH: So you're always here,
watching out for everyone.

857
00:43:41,119 --> 00:43:42,152
Ha.

858
00:43:42,187 --> 00:43:45,221
That's because I never
know when I might explode.

859
00:43:45,257 --> 00:43:46,856
You've got that right.

860
00:43:46,892 --> 00:43:47,657
Pikachu.

861
00:43:47,693 --> 00:43:50,060
Why don't you
two get some sleep.

862
00:43:50,095 --> 00:43:52,295
You're keeping
watch, I am, too.

863
00:43:52,331 --> 00:43:54,264
Pika, Pikachu.

864
00:43:54,333 --> 00:43:55,999
Do as you like.

865
00:43:56,034 --> 00:43:57,067
I will.

866
00:43:57,102 --> 00:43:58,001
Pika-Pika.

867
00:44:07,279 --> 00:44:09,212
[CHUCKLING]

868
00:44:14,853 --> 00:44:16,820
Ta-da!

869
00:44:16,855 --> 00:44:19,789
Your clothes--
they're all clean.

870
00:44:19,825 --> 00:44:20,757
Wow.

871
00:44:20,792 --> 00:44:21,825
Thanks a lot, Serena.

872
00:44:21,860 --> 00:44:22,792
Pikachu!

873
00:44:33,805 --> 00:44:36,573
[BEEPING]

874
00:44:54,726 --> 00:44:56,025
Oh, boy.

875
00:44:56,061 --> 00:44:57,060
This won't be easy.

876
00:45:02,734 --> 00:45:03,666
Gulpin.

877
00:45:03,702 --> 00:45:04,634
Bunnelby.

878
00:45:10,575 --> 00:45:11,007
Yes!

879
00:45:16,014 --> 00:45:16,846
It worked!

880
00:45:31,830 --> 00:45:32,729
BONNIE: Yay!

881
00:45:32,764 --> 00:45:34,697
They brought those
berries for us.

882
00:45:41,039 --> 00:45:41,838
Hm.

883
00:45:41,873 --> 00:45:42,839
Incredible.

884
00:45:42,874 --> 00:45:45,608
I never thought I'd
see humans and Pokemon

885
00:45:45,644 --> 00:45:48,978
getting along together here.

886
00:45:49,014 --> 00:45:52,615
All these Pokemon--
they've been hurt by humans,

887
00:45:52,651 --> 00:45:53,049
haven't they?

888
00:45:53,084 --> 00:45:55,018
Yes, they have.

889
00:45:55,053 --> 00:45:57,787
You, too?

890
00:45:57,823 --> 00:45:59,656
Don't worry about
what happened to me.

891
00:46:06,631 --> 00:46:07,564
All fixed!

892
00:46:07,599 --> 00:46:08,565
Good as new.

893
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:10,967
Next time, we're going
to be working on you.

894
00:46:11,002 --> 00:46:11,968
Working on us?

895
00:46:12,003 --> 00:46:12,836
Pika?

896
00:46:16,575 --> 00:46:17,774
Watch what this one can do.

897
00:46:30,589 --> 00:46:31,721
It's about time.

898
00:46:31,756 --> 00:46:33,756
It worked!

899
00:46:33,792 --> 00:46:34,791
Thanks so much, Gulpin.

900
00:46:41,700 --> 00:46:42,599
Huh?

901
00:46:42,634 --> 00:46:43,600
Pika?

902
00:46:43,635 --> 00:46:45,835
This Gulpin has its reasons.

903
00:46:45,871 --> 00:46:47,804
Anyway, the bands are gone.

904
00:46:47,839 --> 00:46:49,806
Leave.

905
00:46:49,841 --> 00:46:52,041
Even after all
that's happened?

906
00:46:52,077 --> 00:46:54,844
After everybody's starting
to get along so well?

907
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:56,579
Doesn't mean anything.

908
00:46:56,615 --> 00:46:57,680
It does, too.

909
00:46:57,716 --> 00:46:59,716
You only did that because
we were stuck together.

910
00:46:59,751 --> 00:47:01,851
Hey, I really like Pokemon.

911
00:47:01,887 --> 00:47:03,786
I want to protect them, too.

912
00:47:03,822 --> 00:47:05,722
If you're going to
be a Pokemon trainer,

913
00:47:05,757 --> 00:47:08,758
then you've got to learn how
to make Pokemon feel safe.

914
00:47:08,793 --> 00:47:11,995
Right, buddy?
- Pika, pika!

915
00:47:12,030 --> 00:47:15,565
Spare me your pretty
words or I'll blast you.

916
00:47:15,600 --> 00:47:16,699
You try it!

917
00:47:16,735 --> 00:47:18,701
Pika!

918
00:47:18,737 --> 00:47:19,669
Bunnelby.

919
00:47:30,849 --> 00:47:32,582
I'm going to sleep.

920
00:47:32,617 --> 00:47:33,550
Aw.

921
00:48:10,956 --> 00:48:11,888
What?

922
00:48:11,923 --> 00:48:13,823
I brought Poke Puffs.

923
00:48:13,858 --> 00:48:15,792
Serena and Chymia made them.

924
00:48:15,827 --> 00:48:16,726
Pika.

925
00:48:16,761 --> 00:48:18,928
Huh?

926
00:48:18,964 --> 00:48:21,631
You were surprised
back there, weren't you?

927
00:48:21,666 --> 00:48:22,932
They just didn't understand.

928
00:48:22,968 --> 00:48:26,769
Please forgive them.

929
00:48:26,805 --> 00:48:27,770
Sorry, Gulpin.

930
00:48:27,806 --> 00:48:28,738
Pikachu.

931
00:48:34,613 --> 00:48:35,878
This little one
came here after being

932
00:48:35,914 --> 00:48:39,549
abandoned by its trainer.

933
00:48:39,584 --> 00:48:40,717
Pika.

934
00:48:40,752 --> 00:48:43,853
I don't know if anything
happened before that.

935
00:48:43,888 --> 00:48:46,923
He doesn't tell me,
and I don't ask.

936
00:48:46,958 --> 00:48:50,893
The only thing I know is that,
right before its trainer left,

937
00:48:50,929 --> 00:48:53,630
he gave Gulpin a big hug.

938
00:48:59,704 --> 00:49:03,673
All of the Pokemon here have
been wounded by the selfishness

939
00:49:03,708 --> 00:49:05,675
and lies of humans.

940
00:49:05,710 --> 00:49:11,881
They may be laughing now, but
their wounds are deeply-rooted.

941
00:49:11,916 --> 00:49:16,619
And that's the reason
I can't trust humans.

942
00:49:16,655 --> 00:49:20,823
Pokemon are incapable of
lying, but humans are.

943
00:49:20,859 --> 00:49:22,892
And do.

944
00:49:22,927 --> 00:49:23,860
Pika pika.

945
00:49:23,895 --> 00:49:24,827
Pika.

946
00:49:24,863 --> 00:49:25,795
Pika pi.

947
00:49:25,830 --> 00:49:26,763
Really?

948
00:49:26,798 --> 00:49:28,631
This one doesn't lie?

949
00:49:28,667 --> 00:49:29,599
Pika!

950
00:49:29,634 --> 00:49:30,667
Pikachu!

951
00:49:30,702 --> 00:49:31,868
Pikachu.

952
00:49:31,903 --> 00:49:36,673
He fights with all he has
to protect the ones he loves.

953
00:49:36,708 --> 00:49:37,674
Pika pika.

954
00:49:37,709 --> 00:49:38,841
Thank you for that.

955
00:49:38,877 --> 00:49:39,809
You're right.

956
00:49:39,844 --> 00:49:41,044
Pikachu!

957
00:49:41,079 --> 00:49:44,947
Both of you are spewing
nothing but flowery sentiments.

958
00:49:44,983 --> 00:49:46,883
I'm sorry.

959
00:49:46,918 --> 00:49:50,653
Before the others get used
to you, I want you to leave,

960
00:49:50,689 --> 00:49:52,789
though I'm very grateful
to you for what you

961
00:49:52,824 --> 00:49:54,757
did for Magearna and Amaura.

962
00:49:59,698 --> 00:50:00,897
Here.
Go ahead and eat.

963
00:50:10,809 --> 00:50:12,742
Not bad.

964
00:50:12,777 --> 00:50:15,678
If you like it, then why
don't you say you like it?

965
00:50:15,714 --> 00:50:16,646
Pikachu.

966
00:50:16,681 --> 00:50:17,046
Eat.

967
00:50:17,082 --> 00:50:18,014
Both of you.

968
00:50:23,855 --> 00:50:24,854
[RUSTLING]
- Pi?

969
00:50:24,889 --> 00:50:25,788
Pika?

970
00:50:31,696 --> 00:50:33,730
What is that?

971
00:50:33,765 --> 00:50:34,897
[GROWLING]

972
00:50:34,966 --> 00:50:37,633
[ALL SQUEAKING]

973
00:50:42,974 --> 00:50:44,841
[GRUNTING]

974
00:50:48,847 --> 00:50:51,013
[GRUNTING]

975
00:50:51,049 --> 00:50:53,716
[ALL PANTING]

976
00:50:59,057 --> 00:51:01,758
[ALL SCREAMING]

977
00:51:06,765 --> 00:51:07,730
[ALL GASPING]

978
00:51:07,766 --> 00:51:09,665
[GROANING]

979
00:51:10,802 --> 00:51:12,769
Grexit, Talonflame!

980
00:51:12,804 --> 00:51:13,970
Luxray, Greninja!

981
00:51:14,005 --> 00:51:16,939
Woo!

982
00:51:16,975 --> 00:51:19,709
[ALL SHOUTING]

983
00:51:20,712 --> 00:51:23,846
[HOWLING]

984
00:51:23,882 --> 00:51:25,014
Everyone!

985
00:51:25,049 --> 00:51:26,816
[GASPS]

986
00:51:26,851 --> 00:51:28,885
Kanu!

987
00:51:28,920 --> 00:51:30,720
Dreberon.

988
00:51:30,755 --> 00:51:32,688
Jiyoo!

989
00:51:32,724 --> 00:51:33,856
[ALL SCREAMING]

990
00:51:33,892 --> 00:51:38,828
[GRUNTING]

991
00:51:38,863 --> 00:51:39,829
Huh?

992
00:51:39,864 --> 00:51:40,797
Huh?

993
00:51:40,832 --> 00:51:42,965
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

994
00:51:45,937 --> 00:51:46,836
You two.

995
00:51:49,808 --> 00:51:51,674
Well, well.

996
00:51:51,709 --> 00:51:52,675
[CLICK]

997
00:51:52,710 --> 00:51:54,811
[ALL MOANING]

998
00:51:58,016 --> 00:51:58,981
If you resist--

999
00:51:59,017 --> 00:51:59,882
[CLICK]

1000
00:51:59,918 --> 00:52:01,851
[ALL MOANING]

1001
00:52:06,024 --> 00:52:06,989
You're the worst.

1002
00:52:07,025 --> 00:52:07,924
Bega!

1003
00:52:07,959 --> 00:52:09,792
They're humans.

1004
00:52:09,828 --> 00:52:12,862
They think nothing of
the lives of Pokemon.

1005
00:52:12,897 --> 00:52:13,963
Hey!

1006
00:52:13,998 --> 00:52:15,698
I'll blast you!

1007
00:52:15,733 --> 00:52:16,899
Manectric, electrotrain!

1008
00:52:16,935 --> 00:52:19,802
Steelix, use stealth rocket.

1009
00:52:19,871 --> 00:52:22,672
Mey, nethra.

1010
00:52:22,707 --> 00:52:24,674
[SCREAMING]

1011
00:52:24,709 --> 00:52:25,842
[GASPING]

1012
00:52:25,877 --> 00:52:28,845
[GROWLING]

1013
00:52:28,880 --> 00:52:30,847
How dare you?

1014
00:52:34,819 --> 00:52:35,985
[SQUEAKING]

1015
00:52:36,020 --> 00:52:40,723
If you want to help them,
then you should come with us.

1016
00:52:40,758 --> 00:52:43,993
If you do, then
everybody is happy.

1017
00:52:44,028 --> 00:52:45,761
No!

1018
00:52:45,797 --> 00:52:46,796
Don't go, Magearna.

1019
00:52:46,831 --> 00:52:47,897
[GROWLING]

1020
00:52:47,932 --> 00:52:49,699
Then I've no choice.

1021
00:52:49,734 --> 00:52:50,666
[CLICK]

1022
00:52:50,702 --> 00:52:53,703
[ALL SCREAMING]

1023
00:52:53,738 --> 00:52:55,905
Oh, you'll pay for this!

1024
00:52:55,940 --> 00:52:58,708
Oh!

1025
00:52:58,743 --> 00:53:00,843
[BEEPING]

1026
00:53:04,048 --> 00:53:06,849
[GASPS] Magearna!

1027
00:53:06,885 --> 00:53:07,817
Heeda.

1028
00:53:11,990 --> 00:53:13,823
So now you understand.

1029
00:53:13,858 --> 00:53:14,991
[LAUGHS]

1030
00:53:15,026 --> 00:53:16,893
Use psychic.

1031
00:53:16,928 --> 00:53:17,994
Zob.

1032
00:53:18,029 --> 00:53:19,028
Oog nay.

1033
00:53:23,902 --> 00:53:24,867
Googi.

1034
00:53:24,903 --> 00:53:26,769
Magearna!

1035
00:53:26,804 --> 00:53:27,737
Ah.

1036
00:53:34,045 --> 00:53:35,778
[ALL GASPING]

1037
00:53:35,813 --> 00:53:36,979
[PANTING]

1038
00:53:41,819 --> 00:53:44,787
[GROWLING]

1039
00:53:44,822 --> 00:53:46,722
[BEEPING]

1040
00:53:47,091 --> 00:53:49,959
Rollie, Alva.

1041
00:53:49,994 --> 00:53:51,794
Everything's OK.

1042
00:53:51,829 --> 00:53:53,029
All of this is for our kingdom.

1043
00:53:53,064 --> 00:53:54,830
[CHUCKLES]

1044
00:53:54,866 --> 00:53:55,998
[SCOFFS]

1045
00:53:56,034 --> 00:53:58,968
[ROARS]

1046
00:53:59,003 --> 00:54:00,002
Oh.

1047
00:54:00,038 --> 00:54:02,838
Alva, why don't we
tell them everything,

1048
00:54:02,907 --> 00:54:05,841
What an incredible creation
Magearna really is?

1049
00:54:05,877 --> 00:54:06,776
Fine.

1050
00:54:06,811 --> 00:54:07,910
Gengar, mean look.

1051
00:54:07,946 --> 00:54:09,879
Gah.

1052
00:54:09,914 --> 00:54:10,880
[BEEPING]

1053
00:54:10,915 --> 00:54:11,847
Huh?

1054
00:54:11,883 --> 00:54:12,848
Ah.

1055
00:54:12,884 --> 00:54:15,017
[BEEPING]

1056
00:54:15,853 --> 00:54:16,786
Gah.

1057
00:54:19,924 --> 00:54:21,958
- [EVIL LAUGH]
- Wait a minute.

1058
00:54:21,993 --> 00:54:24,760
You don't have to
remove its soul-heart.

1059
00:54:24,796 --> 00:54:27,763
That's just as long as
Magearna becomes a spear.

1060
00:54:27,799 --> 00:54:29,799
Nicholas said that-- ah!

1061
00:54:29,834 --> 00:54:32,568
All that I really
need is its soul-heart.

1062
00:54:32,603 --> 00:54:33,135
You can't!

1063
00:54:33,171 --> 00:54:35,037
If you remove it, then--

1064
00:54:40,845 --> 00:54:43,012
[CHUCKLES]

1065
00:54:47,018 --> 00:54:49,018
Alva, what happened?

1066
00:54:49,053 --> 00:54:49,986
It's gone.

1067
00:54:50,021 --> 00:54:51,053
[GASPS]

1068
00:54:51,089 --> 00:54:53,923
Gengar, kindly
return Magearna.

1069
00:54:53,958 --> 00:54:55,992
[SNARLS]

1070
00:54:59,764 --> 00:55:00,696
[GASPS]

1071
00:55:00,732 --> 00:55:02,832
[SHOUTING]

1072
00:55:02,867 --> 00:55:07,570
Chymia, your presence is
not required for my plan.

1073
00:55:07,605 --> 00:55:08,838
Farewell.

1074
00:55:08,873 --> 00:55:10,539
Use hyperbeam.

1075
00:55:10,575 --> 00:55:12,541
[SHOUTING]

1076
00:55:18,883 --> 00:55:20,783
How could you lie to me?

1077
00:55:20,818 --> 00:55:22,752
It wasn't for the kingdom!

1078
00:55:22,787 --> 00:55:26,956
Yes, it was all done for the
glory of the Kingdom of Azoth,

1079
00:55:26,991 --> 00:55:29,592
my ideal one, of course.

1080
00:55:29,627 --> 00:55:30,960
[GASPS]

1081
00:55:30,995 --> 00:55:32,828
Gengar, hypnosis.

1082
00:55:32,864 --> 00:55:35,698
[SNARLING]

1083
00:55:59,741 --> 00:56:02,575
They used dig and safeguard.

1084
00:56:02,610 --> 00:56:03,709
Thank you, everyone.

1085
00:56:03,745 --> 00:56:05,745
Re pow.

1086
00:56:05,780 --> 00:56:06,712
Magearna!

1087
00:56:17,425 --> 00:56:19,692
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

1088
00:56:40,414 --> 00:56:41,580
Volcanion.

1089
00:56:41,616 --> 00:56:42,548
Weepa.

1090
00:56:49,757 --> 00:56:51,624
If it's soul-heart
is returned,

1091
00:56:51,659 --> 00:56:53,626
Magearna should be revived.

1092
00:56:53,661 --> 00:56:54,593
[GASPING]

1093
00:56:57,765 --> 00:56:58,764
Everyone on board.

1094
00:57:02,403 --> 00:57:05,704
Prince Raleigh, I thought
that you would understand,

1095
00:57:05,740 --> 00:57:07,640
that you would be
able to comprehend

1096
00:57:07,675 --> 00:57:09,675
my noblest of dreams.

1097
00:57:09,710 --> 00:57:12,578
There's no reason to
make such a big fuss.

1098
00:57:12,613 --> 00:57:14,547
We're only talking
about one Pokemon.

1099
00:57:22,723 --> 00:57:26,325
[GASPS] It's Magearna.

1100
00:57:26,360 --> 00:57:28,627
I can sense it right from here.

1101
00:57:28,663 --> 00:57:29,595
Oh, Magearna.

1102
00:57:29,630 --> 00:57:31,630
It's crying.

1103
00:57:31,666 --> 00:57:34,600
In that case, it's
retrieved the soul-heart.

1104
00:57:34,635 --> 00:57:36,669
[INAUDIBLE]

1105
00:57:36,704 --> 00:57:38,637
Gengar, psychic.

1106
00:57:38,673 --> 00:57:40,339
Gah!

1107
00:57:40,374 --> 00:57:42,808
You're even less
than useless to me.

1108
00:57:42,844 --> 00:57:44,643
[ALL MOANING]

1109
00:57:44,679 --> 00:57:47,613
[SCREAMING]

1110
00:58:01,362 --> 00:58:03,429
VOLCANION: That
field of flowers,

1111
00:58:03,464 --> 00:58:07,366
that's where I met Magearna
for the very first time.

1112
00:58:07,401 --> 00:58:09,635
Wasn't it 500 years ago?

1113
00:58:09,670 --> 00:58:12,605
I don't know how you
humans measure time.

1114
00:58:12,640 --> 00:58:14,740
But it's a story from
the ancient past.

1115
00:58:29,790 --> 00:58:32,791
Then, as now, the
plateaus. was my home,

1116
00:58:32,827 --> 00:58:36,695
and that of many, many
other troubled Pokemon.

1117
00:58:36,731 --> 00:58:40,699
Oftentimes, I would check the
area for Pokemon that were lost

1118
00:58:40,735 --> 00:58:42,668
and had collapsed
from exhaustion.

1119
00:59:01,389 --> 00:59:03,455
Magearna was the first
one I met that wasn't

1120
